Program: Last Word
Title: Tony Booth, Liliane Bettencourt, William G Stewart, Tom Petty
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b096jkg0
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 8 Oct 2017
Matthew Bannister on The actor Tony Booth, best known for playing Alf Garnett's left wing son-in-law in the TV comedy Till Death Us Do Part - and notorious for his womanising and heavy drinking. His daughter Cherie Blair shares her memories. Lillian Bettencourt who was the richest woman in the world - as heiress to the L'Oreal cosmetics group. She was also embroiled in a bitter court battle over how her fortune should be divided. William G. Stewart, best known as the host of the long running TV quiz "Fifteen to One", He was also a respected producer and director. And the rock star Tom Petty - best known for hits like "Free Fallin'" and "I Won't Back Down". Show less